pine ridge reservation
south dakata
march,1890

36
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:42,390
10 years had passed since robert
and clara nhad left pennsylvania.

37
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:46,620
robert had seen the land's
promise turn bitter,

38
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:50,720
but he was determined to carry on
the best way he knew how.

39
00:04:51,050 --> 00:04:54,710
yeah,the burial scaffolds
are outlawed now.

40
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:59,160
lot of things have changed since
they split up the reservation last year.

41
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:05,090
now you've got pockets
of white settlers all over.

42
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,840
i imagined it
so differently.

43
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:12,540
10 years
is a long time,george.

44
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,530
stand aside,please.

45
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:31,100
you give something.

46
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:34,020
these rations are property
of the u.s. government.

47
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,120
i'm just the man
who delivers them.

48
00:05:36,150 --> 00:05:38,700
government
have no stomach.

49
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:41,920
you're going to have to get
your rations from agent royer.

50
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:43,690
royer.

51
00:05:44,890 --> 00:05:46,950
i'm sorry for your plight,

52
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,520
but there's nothing
i can do.

53
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:51,790
now please stand aside.

54
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,850
when your children
cry for food,

55
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:57,560
you will do nothing?

56
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:32,280
do you people
want your rations or not?

57
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:34,980
pay attention. next.

58
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,550
no distribution
till the line is straight.

59
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:43,140
can't you people understand
what straight means?

60
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,180
next.

61
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:58,070
metal breasts

62
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:10,240
what's the news,
wheeler?

63
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:12,410
well,you're the reporters.

64
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:14,300
you tell me.

65
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:17,050
looks like he's got
nothing for us...

66
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,380
as usual.

67
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:21,510
well,i'm sorry
to disappoint your readers.

68
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:25,890
you'd think with all the hauling
you do between here and standing rock

69
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:29,060
you'd see at least one
young buck on the warpath.

70
00:08:29,650 --> 00:08:33,810
you know,you boys could stand
to get out of the agency for a spell.

71
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:34,780
why don't you talk
to george?

72
00:08:34,810 --> 00:08:38,470
he just arrived here on the
overnight out of new york city.

73
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:42,620
i'm sure he'd be happy
to share his impressions.

74
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,380
next.

75
00:08:55,430 --> 00:08:56,640
royer around?

76
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:59,020
you know he never shows
his face on issue day.

77
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:00,480
next.

78
00:09:00,530 --> 00:09:04,350
only coffee,flour,
and blanket this month.

79
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:09,740
- no meat?
- no meat,no sugar.

80
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:13,730
- flour,coffee,blanket.next.
- want bacon.

81
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:16,210
children very sick.
need food.

82
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,590
bacon is meat.

83
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:20,260
next.

84
00:09:20,330 --> 00:09:22,020
ingrates.

85
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:25,720
you holding back
on us here,wheeler?

86
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,650
why i want to talk
to royer.

87
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,820
a little business matter.

88
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:31,710
next.

89
00:09:36,370 --> 00:09:40,750
no long hair.
no more than one wife.

90
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,850
no heathenish ways.

91
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,040
no old religion.

92
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:46,690
no drinking.

93
00:09:46,710 --> 00:09:49,990
no language but english.

94
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:52,150
if you can accept
these things,

95
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:55,850
then step over there
and pick up your uniforms.

96
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:10,410
indian police are doing well.

97
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:15,150
well,can't blame 'em for
wanting something better,i suppose.

98
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:17,880
things took a bad turn
back in '88.

99
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:20,580
crops failed
two years running.

100
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,890
and the indians weren't
the only ones who suffered.

101
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:24,960
we were
damn near wiped out.

102
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,410
but clara,the boy,
and me,

103
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:29,380
we saw ourselves
through.

104
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,500
she can't wait
to see you.

105
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:34,930
"to see a world
in a grain of sand,

106
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:37,690
"and heaven
in a wild flower,

107
00:10:37,730 --> 00:10:41,290
"hold infinity
in the palm of your hand

108
00:10:41,310 --> 00:10:44,420
and eternity in an hour."

109
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:46,090
isn't that
a wonderful thought?

110
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:49,500
to see a world
in a grain of sand.

111
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:53,020
how many times do we look
without seeing?

112
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:58,120
poetry teaches us
to see things in a different way.

113
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,740
there's no reason
to be afraid of it.

114
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:02,800
who wants to try?

115
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:11,510
read among
yourselves. quietly.

116
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:26,860
quite a dapper eastern
gentleman you've become.

117
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:29,950
yeah. it's good
to see you,miss clara.

118
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:32,560
don't be so formal.
it's just plain clara now.

119
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:34,190
yes,ma'am.

120
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:36,450
i believe i'll let you two
get reacquainted.

121
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,920
i've got some business
with royer.

122
00:11:40,870 --> 00:11:43,220
come meet my pupils.

123
00:11:47,570 --> 00:11:52,550
class,i want you to meet
george voices that carry.

124
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,870
george was a student of mine
a long time ago.

125
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,810
he used to live here
in pine ridge.

126
00:11:57,840 --> 00:12:00,190
now he's come back,
i hope to teach.

127
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:02,130
no,not to teach.

128
00:12:02,390 --> 00:12:04,110
to learn.

129
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:15,190
i have lived among
the white men for many years,

130
00:12:15,230 --> 00:12:17,770
but i am still lakota...

131
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:19,760
like you,

132
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:23,560
and there is much
to learn from our people.

133
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:29,000
congress sets the policy,
mr. wheeler.

134
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:31,890
i'm merely charged with
carrying out its intent.

135
00:12:31,930 --> 00:12:35,740
the beef allotment to this agency
has been reduced by one million pounds.

136
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:38,870
washington takes its census
numbers quite seriously.

137
00:12:38,930 --> 00:12:41,240
well,it seems pretty damn
short-sighted,if you ask me.

138
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:44,250
and what about
this bill of lading?

139
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:47,370
- couldn't bring myself to refuse 'em.
- they were starving.

140
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,250
i'll pay for
the lost goods in full.

141
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:52,770
your charity only exacerbates
a difficult situation,mr. wheeler.

142
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:55,280
you may want to have
a look at this.

143
00:12:58,990 --> 00:13:01,790
my colleague at standing rock,
mr. mclaughlin,

144
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:04,610
informs me that rumors
of an indian messiah

145
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,500
are spreading like wildfire.

146
00:13:06,540 --> 00:13:08,990
he reassures me
it is only a minor annoyance,

147
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,660
but i have my doubts.

148
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:14,140
well,no telling where
desperate people will find hope.

149
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:16,060
i can only do so much,
mr. wheeler.

150
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:18,380
more than that
i am not allowed.

151
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:22,020
these people are suspicious
of any changes.

152
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,140
your predecessor
colonel gallagher

153
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:27,090
was a hard man,
but fair.

154
00:13:27,130 --> 00:13:28,770
- they'd come to respect him.
- be that as it may

155
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,520
the new administration has
selected me to see to its affairs.

156
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:32,850
well,maybe when you've been here a little longer--

157
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,770
as you say.

158
00:13:38,490 --> 00:13:40,330
is there anything else
you wish to discuss?

159
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:41,860
no.

160
00:13:42,130 --> 00:13:44,360
no,i figure
we're through.

161
00:13:44,460 --> 00:13:46,430
i'll say good day then.

162
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:55,240
let's go,people.
keep it moving.

163
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:36,600
where is your mother?

164
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:42,250
our mother can not feed us

165
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:25,840
sitting bull's camp
standing rock reservation

166
00:15:57,780 --> 00:16:00,100
i'm looking for red lance,

167
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:04,270
son of white crow,
grandson of running fox.

168
00:16:04,990 --> 00:16:07,360
who looks for
red lance?

169
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:11,790
his brother,
voices that carry

170
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:40,610
little brother,
look at you.

171
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:44,220
did they drink your blood,
turn you into a wasichu?

172
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:49,510
the wasichu
did not defeat us.

173
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:53,950
it was the wind and the snow of our
grandmother's land that was our enemy.

174
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,750
and our father
and grandfather?

175
00:17:09,850 --> 00:17:14,760
i'm sorry,brother,
truly.

176
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:19,820
sitting bull was the last
to give up his rifle and horse.

177
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:22,620
the long knives,
they promised us land,

178
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:24,420
but they lied.

179
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,690
they made us prisoners.

180
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,410
all of you?

181
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:32,350
two years the soldiers
watched over our tipis,

182
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,920
and then long hair
came and took us.

183
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:39,210
buffalo bill.

184
00:17:40,210 --> 00:17:43,910
he said he would
pay us to be indians.

185
00:17:44,610 --> 00:17:49,940
he showed us how to make faces
and shake our tomahawks around.

186
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,870
i've come to stay,
brother.

187
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:01,200
this is good.

188
00:18:05,610 --> 00:18:09,600
the messiah's medicine
is powerful

189
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:14,750
many saw their relatives
in the next world

190
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:20,090
this dance will make
many problems

191
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:25,250
does the messiah say we
will fight the white man?

192
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:26,850
no

193
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:31,260
when the time comes,
the white man will go away

194
00:18:34,570 --> 00:18:39,240
let the dance be
taught to our people

195
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:46,770
you believe in this man
wovoka's vision?

196
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:52,990
i believe in hope

197
00:18:56,390 --> 00:18:59,930
june,1890

198
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,970
red cloud could stop this
nonsense with a word,

199
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:24,250
but the old codger says
it's nothing to do with him.

200
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:26,260
as i understand
the dogma,sir,

201
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:28,880
it shares many of our own
christian principles.

202
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,870
a harmless version of their
outlawed sun dance.

203
00:19:30,910 --> 00:19:32,800
looks more like
a war dance to me.

204
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:37,490
and you,mr. wheeler,do you consider
this demonstration harmless?

205
00:19:49,110 --> 00:19:51,740
well,this ought to be
interesting,boys.

206
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:22,090
i don't see
any call for that.

207
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:25,190
i'll thank you to stay out
of government business,
mr. wheeler.

208
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:30,050
this obscene display
will cease immediately!

209
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:37,770
this prayer.
white people pray,

210
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:39,800
go heaven.

211
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,870
we go heaven,too.

212
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:45,240
you will stop dancing
and disperse!

213
00:20:56,970 --> 00:21:02,090
we should call him...

214
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:06,460
young man afraid of indians

215
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:22,250
get outta my way.

216
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:26,090
take this down,mr. duffy.
make it fast,lang.

217
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,430
to the editor,
new york herald.

218
00:21:27,470 --> 00:21:30,750
uh,"the long-awaited violence
here finally exploded today--"

219
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:31,800
"exploded."
i like that.

220
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:34,390
"when a band of armed hostiles
confronted the government's agent.

221
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:35,930
"against impossible odds,

222
00:21:35,970 --> 00:21:38,260
"agent royer acquitted
himself without bloodshed

223
00:21:38,290 --> 00:21:41,440
"and brought a well-deserved end
to the...pagan spectacle

224
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:42,870
known as the ghost dance.

225
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,880
"it is common knowledge in these parts
that the sioux never dance this.

226
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:51,290
foul dance except for one purpose:
