00:25:16,530 --> 00:25:20,080
huh?
that was perfect.

275
00:25:20,110 --> 00:25:21,480
drink up,gentlemen.

276
00:25:21,510 --> 00:25:23,310
thank you so much.

277
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:27,940
they are gonna
eat this up in new york.

278
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:43,820
you got permission
for that?

279
00:25:43,860 --> 00:25:47,000
i got permission.
ask royer.

280
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:51,310
you might have
seen her yourself.

281
00:25:51,730 --> 00:25:54,580
i don't keep track
of faces.

282
00:25:58,980 --> 00:26:02,850
standing rock reservation

283
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:20,340
you let the fire go out.

284
00:26:20,390 --> 00:26:22,460
didn't notice.

285
00:26:24,670 --> 00:26:26,850
what good are all
these white man's books

286
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,330
if you don't know
when you're cold?

287
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:31,530
it's not that cold.

288
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:46,940
you,uh...
read all these books?

289
00:26:47,170 --> 00:26:48,910
there's much
to learn from them.

290
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:51,030
what good
is this knowledge?

291
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:53,980
you have many questions,
red lance,but

292
00:26:54,010 --> 00:26:55,750
you have no desire
to hear my answers.

293
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:58,250
and you do not
wish to learn.

294
00:26:58,310 --> 00:27:00,310
i've told you.

295
00:27:00,350 --> 00:27:03,310
the ghost dance
is only superstition.

296
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,560
spirits can't
help our people.

297
00:27:04,610 --> 00:27:07,180
only we can do that
for ourselves.

298
00:27:07,210 --> 00:27:12,110
you do not have ears.
you will not listen.

299
00:27:17,570 --> 00:27:20,710
i bring you the
promise of a day

300
00:27:21,690 --> 00:27:26,740
when no white man
will treat us badly again

301
00:27:28,770 --> 00:27:31,530
when the sacred dead
will live again

302
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:38,980
it is impossible for a
dead man to live again

303
00:27:42,430 --> 00:27:46,660
the white hair at the
agency,mclanghlin

304
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:50,940
says soldiers will
stop this dance

305
00:27:52,630 --> 00:27:56,440
the soldiers will
harm no one

306
00:27:57,170 --> 00:28:00,950
the messiah has
sent me a vision

307
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:05,290
the shirt is powerful medicine

308
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:11,240
it will stop the soldiers' bullets

309
00:28:11,870 --> 00:28:17,010
red cloud and big foot's
people are dancing

310
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:23,440
sitting bull's people
must also dance

311
00:28:25,820 --> 00:28:27,420
cotton will not stop
a lead bullet

312
00:28:27,450 --> 00:28:30,080
no matter what
kicking bear says.

313
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:40,520
to say "believe"
or "do not believe,"

314
00:28:40,550 --> 00:28:42,970
this is the white man's way.

315
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:48,800
let them dance

316
00:29:30,340 --> 00:29:32,080
this pernicious item,
gentlemen,

317
00:29:32,110 --> 00:29:34,480
is known as
a ghost shirt.

318
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:35,830
among its many powers,

319
00:29:35,860 --> 00:29:38,680
it is alleged
to stop bullets.

320
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:41,510
so let us not deny further
that trouble is imminent.

321
00:29:41,540 --> 00:29:44,650
every one of these hostiles
is prepared to use violence.

322
00:29:44,690 --> 00:29:46,440
i've been
among them before.

323
00:29:46,470 --> 00:29:48,050
question is: what are you
going to do about it?

324
00:29:48,090 --> 00:29:52,520
we can do nothing until the interior
department and the war department

325
00:29:52,550 --> 00:29:54,630
provide explicit
instructions.

326
00:29:54,670 --> 00:29:57,090
until then,
we must all wait

327
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,050
and be on our guard
at the first sign of outbreak.

328
00:30:00,070 --> 00:30:02,220
if you just
leave it alone,

329
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,440
and likely as not,

330
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:06,630
the whole craze will just
die out on its own.

331
00:30:06,690 --> 00:30:09,490
mr. mclaughlin at standing rock
believes that

332
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:13,960
as long as a single malcontent
like sitting bull remains at large,

333
00:30:13,990 --> 00:30:16,340
that we cannot
be secure.

334
00:30:16,370 --> 00:30:17,190
and i concur.

335
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:18,870
if you lock up
the ringleaders--

336
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:22,410
then you're gonna have
a real problem on your hands...

337
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:26,290
not just in
your imagination.

338
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,630
is this a ghost shirt?

339
00:30:51,490 --> 00:30:54,290
ghost shirt,savvy?

340
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,600
ghost shirt.

341
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:04,320
what will you
take for it?

342
00:31:06,350 --> 00:31:09,360
you...and me.

343
00:31:09,390 --> 00:31:11,670
we make trade.

344
00:31:14,410 --> 00:31:18,390
- trade.
- that's right.

345
00:31:23,220 --> 00:31:25,950
you want my camera.

346
00:31:28,150 --> 00:31:30,560
what's a squaw know
about taking pictures.

347
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:31,620
i'll tell you what.

348
00:31:31,660 --> 00:31:33,850
i'll give you...

349
00:31:34,730 --> 00:31:38,290
two american dollars.

350
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:42,500
no can do.

351
00:31:42,530 --> 00:31:43,860
it's not for sale.

352
00:31:43,890 --> 00:31:46,070
hey,another camera's
easy to come by.

353
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:49,560
where in the hell else are you
gonna find another ghost shirt?

354
00:32:04,310 --> 00:32:08,470
lady,you got yourself
a deal.

355
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:26,190
- how about that?
- that's nice.real nice.

356
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:29,380
- and bulletproof.
- better not try it.

357
00:34:09,710 --> 00:34:11,550
needs mending.

358
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:13,770
we best see to it.

359
00:34:13,830 --> 00:34:15,890
look at that.

360
00:34:19,450 --> 00:34:22,190
i'll be doggoned.

361
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:26,240
i'm gonna go back
to the barn

362
00:34:26,260 --> 00:34:29,240
and get some extra wire
and tools and whatnot,

363
00:34:29,270 --> 00:34:31,580
and we'll--we'll fix her.

364
00:34:34,380 --> 00:34:36,330
they busted in.

365
00:34:36,390 --> 00:34:39,270
won't they just
bust out again?

366
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:42,630
no,i don't think so.

367
00:34:42,680 --> 00:34:44,870
well,why not?

368
00:34:45,970 --> 00:34:50,760
maybe because this
is the land they remember.

369
00:36:26,260 --> 00:36:28,430
father.

370
00:36:39,940 --> 00:36:43,630
it makes my heart glad
to see you with these children.

371
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:46,510
you are a good mother
to them.

372
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:49,890
as you were to me.

373
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:57,730
my wandering must have
caused you great worry and pain.

374
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:00,860
forgive me.

375
00:37:01,590 --> 00:37:06,500
you were always
our family's seeker.

376
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:10,660
but the road you have chosen
has not been easy.

377
00:37:11,110 --> 00:37:12,820
they were
so many times

378
00:37:12,850 --> 00:37:16,390
when i thought
it was impossible to go on.

379
00:37:16,420 --> 00:37:19,790
but i remembered
your strength,

380
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:24,680
how you carried on even
after we thought father had died.

381
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:28,610
that was the greatest
gift you gave to me.

382
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:33,230
you helped me to endure.

383
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:36,480
to live.

384
00:37:44,690 --> 00:37:48,300
when you're ready,
you look through here,

385
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:51,590
then you press this button.

386
00:37:51,750 --> 00:37:55,070
i'm happy you
still take pictures.

387
00:37:56,780 --> 00:37:59,500
i didn't...

388
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:02,840
after sand creek.

389
00:38:13,050 --> 00:38:15,720
but it is
all different now.

390
00:38:42,830 --> 00:38:47,480
"when in disgrace
with fortune in men's eyes,

391
00:38:47,530 --> 00:38:51,390
"i all alone be weep
my outcast state,

392
00:38:51,430 --> 00:38:55,160
"and trouble deaf heaven
with my bootless cries,

393
00:38:55,210 --> 00:38:59,830
desiring this man's art,
and that man's scope."

394
00:39:26,010 --> 00:39:28,210
what do you
say now,mr. wheeler?

395
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:29,680
do you still
think this craze,

396
00:39:29,710 --> 00:39:32,020
as you call it,
is dying out?

397
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:34,130
well,i have put up
with quite enough of this lunacy,

398
00:39:34,170 --> 00:39:36,410
and i intend
to do something about it.

399
00:39:36,470 --> 00:39:39,060
duffy,take this down.

400
00:39:39,100 --> 00:39:41,870
to the commissioner
of indian affairs in washington,

401
00:39:41,910 --> 00:39:43,690
wild indians are dancing,

402
00:39:43,710 --> 00:39:45,520
and cannot be
induced to stop.

403
00:39:45,550 --> 00:39:48,150
the ghost dance has now
assumed such proportions,

404
00:39:48,180 --> 00:39:50,640
both in the number,and the spirit
of the adherents,

405
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:52,970
that it is entirely beyond the control
of the agent and the police force

406
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:56,800
who are openly defied
by the dancers.

407
00:39:56,820 --> 00:40:01,010
the employees and the government property
of this agency has no protection,

408
00:40:01,040 --> 00:40:03,470
and we are at the mercy
of these dancers.

409
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:06,200
we need protection,
and we need it now.

410
00:40:06,230 --> 00:40:08,660
this agent suggests
sending a body of troops

411
00:40:08,700 --> 00:40:10,660
sufficient to arrest
the leaders therein,

412
00:40:10,710 --> 00:40:11,990
and imprison them,

413
00:40:12,030 --> 00:40:14,650
and disarm the balance
of the reservation.

414
00:40:14,690 --> 00:40:17,010
nothing short of
a thousand troops,

415
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:18,940
backed by
the proper artillery,

416
00:40:18,970 --> 00:40:23,220
will stop the proliferation
of this diabolical dance.

417
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:53,870
god bless ya,boys!

418
00:41:37,290 --> 00:41:41,720
december,1890

419
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:09,180
colonel forsyth,

420
00:42:09,210 --> 00:42:12,830
we are friends
of the agent.

421
00:42:12,870 --> 00:42:16,510
we are friends
of the soldiers.

422
00:42:16,550 --> 00:42:21,860
the great father's friends
are my friends,too.

423
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:26,310
i want not any trouble
for my people.

424
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:29,920
we have no guns
to fight with.

425
00:42:29,950 --> 00:42:32,650
we have
nothing to eat.

426
00:42:32,670 --> 00:42:35,550
we are too poor
to do anything.

427
00:42:35,590 --> 00:42:38,890
you're not too poor
to dance your ghost dance.

428
00:42:38,950 --> 00:42:43,370
many say i have
been to this dance.

429
00:42:43,390 --> 00:42:45,540
that is not right.

430
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:48,020
my eyes are sore.

431
00:42:48,060 --> 00:42:51,000
they do not
see very well.

432
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:55,160
but,when they better,
i go and see.

433
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,990
we do not ask you to see it,
we ask you to stop it.

434
00:42:58,030 --> 00:43:01,320
when winter comes,
dancing stops.

435
00:43:01,370 --> 00:43:04,890
there will be
no problems.

436
00:43:05,100 --> 00:43:07,330
many of your people have
taken to the badlands.

437
00:43:07,370 --> 00:43:09,020
if they do not return

438
00:43:09,050 --> 00:43:12,980
we'll have no choice
but to consider them hostile.

439
00:43:13,770 --> 00:43:19,060
they think the soldiers
have come to kill us.

440
00:43:19,100 --> 00:43:20,920
i not believe this,

441
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:25,270
but they are afraid
for their families.

442
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:27,550
you understand.

443
00:43:27,590 --> 00:43:29,480
and the warriors
with them?

444
00:43:29,530 --> 00:43:31,320
what's to keep them
from joining up with kicking bear

445
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:33,620
or the other
renegades?

446
00:43:34,020 --> 00:43:38,970
that is all i have to
say about this question.

